WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.016
To be effective, four facets of CQ must be developed.

00:00:05.016 --> 00:00:10.032
First, let us examine Metacognitive CQ, which is the mental

00:00:10.032 --> 00:00:15.048
capability to acquire and understand cultural knowledge, verifying assumptions during

00:00:15.048 --> 00:00:20.064
cross-cultural interactions. Moving on to the next block, Cognitive CQ

00:00:20.064 --> 00:00:25.079
is the general knowledge about different cultures, norms, and business

00:00:25.079 --> 00:00:30.095
practices. Next, we have Motivational CQ, which is the interest,

00:00:30.095 --> 00:00:35.111
confidence, and persistence in adapting to new cultural environments, even

00:00:35.111 --> 00:00:40.127
when friction occurs. Finally, Behavioral CQ is the capability to

00:00:40.127 --> 00:00:45.143
exhibit appropriate verbal and non-verbal actions.
